text: “never used set lists, shows always organically grown, flow, song like Combination Lock, sometimes work opener… something hard drop , something … don’t know … just didn’t seem fit general movement set …” - Ian Mackaye, 12/2/2022 article offers visualisation transitions songs Fugazi performed live using metadata Fugazi Live Series. every pair songs performed sequence transition first song second song. instance, show 20 songs 19 transitions pairs songs. listening Fugazi Live Series , seems transitions much common others, hard tell sure without listening whole series looking data. Let’s quick look data see find. raw data processed previously use data one row per song performance Repeatr1 dataframe Repeatr package.

title: Combination Lock
text: Let’s get data, limit columns using, look first rows. order look transitions songs, let’s get list songs performed show match song onto song performed next show. way one row data transition songs. simple check see number rows second dataframe correct. number transitions equal number songs minus one show, total number transitions series equal total number songs series minus total number shows series. Now let’s summarise data count many times transition occurs.
code: mydf1 <- Repeatr1 %>%   select(gid,song_number,song) %>%   rename(song1 = song)  print(paste0("There are ", nrow(mydf1), " rows in this dataframe.")) #> [1] "There are 23279 rows in this dataframe."  head(mydf1) #> # A tibble: 6 × 3 #>   gid                 song_number song1             #>   <chr>                     <dbl> <chr>             #> 1 aalst-belgium-92390           1 intro             #> 2 aalst-belgium-92390           2 turnover          #> 3 aalst-belgium-92390           3 brendan #1        #> 4 aalst-belgium-92390           4 merchandise       #> 5 aalst-belgium-92390           5 sieve-fisted find #> 6 aalst-belgium-92390           6 and the same mydf2 <- Repeatr1 %>%   select(gid,song_number,song) %>%   mutate(song_number = song_number-1) %>%   rename(song2 = song)  mydf3 <- mydf1 %>%   left_join(mydf2) %>%   filter(is.na(song2)==FALSE) %>%   rename(transition_number = song_number) #> Joining with `by = join_by(gid, song_number)`  print(paste0("There are ", nrow(mydf3), " rows in this dataframe.")) #> [1] "There are 22377 rows in this dataframe."  head(mydf3) #> # A tibble: 6 × 4 #>   gid                 transition_number song1             song2             #>   <chr>                           <dbl> <chr>             <chr>             #> 1 aalst-belgium-92390                 1 intro             turnover          #> 2 aalst-belgium-92390                 2 turnover          brendan #1        #> 3 aalst-belgium-92390                 3 brendan #1        merchandise       #> 4 aalst-belgium-92390                 4 merchandise       sieve-fisted find #> 5 aalst-belgium-92390                 5 sieve-fisted find and the same      #> 6 aalst-belgium-92390                 6 and the same      interlude 1 checknumberofshows <- Repeatr1 %>%   group_by(gid) %>%   summarise(songs = n()) %>%   ungroup()  numberofshows <- nrow(checknumberofshows)  print(paste0("There are ", numberofshows, " rows in this dataframe.")) #> [1] "There are 900 rows in this dataframe."  head(checknumberofshows) #> # A tibble: 6 × 2 #>   gid                          songs #>   <chr>                        <int> #> 1 aalst-belgium-92390             23 #> 2 aberdeen-scotland-50499         27 #> 3 adelaide-australia-111193       17 #> 4 adelaide-australia-111296       29 #> 5 adelaide-sa-australia-102291    26 #> 6 akron-oh-usa-62890              26  numberofsongs <- sum(checknumberofshows$songs)  numberoftransitions <- numberofsongs - numberofshows  print(paste0("There are ", numberofsongs, " songs, ", numberofshows, " shows, and ", numberoftransitions, " transitions between songs in the Fugazi Live Series data."  )) #> [1] "There are 23279 songs, 900 shows, and 22379 transitions between songs in the Fugazi Live Series data." transitions <- mydf3 %>%   select(song1, song2) %>%   rename(from = song1) %>%   rename(to = song2)  transitions <- transitions %>%   group_by(from, to) %>%   summarize(count = n()) %>%   ungroup() #> `summarise()` has grouped output by 'from'. what: Tests whether differences between pairs of model parameters are significant or not. — diffr
title: Tests whether differences between pairs of model parameters are significant or not. — diffr
text: function finds standard error difference two coefficients terms variances covariance: myse <- (sqrt(myvar1 + myvar2 - 2*mycov)) proceeds calculate z-statistic: myz <- (mycoefdiff)/myse z-statistic 1.96 greater indicate difference coefficients significant 95% level confidence. index numbers based model coefficient table comes straight model, sorting. function return one-row dataframe following columns: var1, var2, coefindex1, coefindex2, mycoef1, mycoef2, mycoefdiff, myz, myp, lower95ci, upper95ci coefficient index 0 interpreted referring omitted constant.

title: Tests whether differences between pairs of model parameters are significant or not. — diffr
